				\begin{document}$$\bar v$$\end{document}v¯ from 2.3 bp s−1 to 14.5 bp s−1 (SD = 10.5 bp s−1; Nm = 17, Nc = 15) and increases the fraction of 1 s intervals that exhibit slipping from 16% to 31.6%. This suggests that with 0.17 mM γ-S-ATP many of the slips are attributable to transient dissociation of γ-S-ATP.

