In the absence of nucleotides, the DNA slips very rapidly (Figs. 2 and 3a) and to track it the optical trap had to be moved at the maximum speed our instrument allows (~730 nm s−1). The average slipping velocity is \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
